page.title: 19WILDLIFE IN HIGHCLIFFE
page.content:
In Highcliffe we see a lot of birds. Our most common bird is the seagull but we also see sparrows, blackbirds crows and herons. We have seen 22 large trees with more than 5 crows and blackbirds nesting. In the winter we see a lot of robins. We see a lot of rodents and our most common is the rabbit. We sometimes see foxes. We have heathland where we see lizards. We have a lot of trees in Highcliffe. Our most common tree is the pine tree, but we also see oak, silver birch and beech. We also see many gorse and rhododendron bushes. We have two commons and we have heathland on one of them. All our commons are interesting because they have a lot of birds, rodents, animals and trees.
By Robert Letchford, William Nicholls and James Burton.
